text: The stall besides offering delicious grilled satay also sells a variety of popular local Malay dishes such as gado gado, tahu goreng, mee rebus, nasi lemak, mee soto.
Simply put the best satay I ate in Singapore - and I ate a lot! Such lovely people.
Must try! Honest and friendly old man. Tasty satay, transparent pricing compare to another store.
The best malay stall for breakfast overlooking lagoon.
Tasty no frills. Min buy is 10 skewers at 0.80$ each. I would get this again.
